We see issues with TypeScript treating interfaces and classes equal and extension writer run it this... We should help and accept data that looks OK and convert it into instances of our classes, ala

```
class CompletionItem {
 static adopt(item:CompletionItem) {
  if(item instanceof CompletionItem) {
     return item;
   } else if(item) {
     return new CompletionItem(item.label, ... more data...)
  }
 }
}
```

Instead of instanceof-checks we should first adopt and then check.

